WEBVTT

00:02.802 --> 00:04.571
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.637 --> 00:06.272
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:06.339 --> 00:07.841
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.907 --> 00:09.609
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:09.676 --> 00:11.511
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:11.578 --> 00:13.780
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:13.847 --> 00:15.215
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.281 --> 00:16.850
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.916 --> 00:18.385
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:18.451 --> 00:20.153
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:20.220 --> 00:21.688
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.755 --> 00:23.456
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:23.523 --> 00:24.691
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.758 --> 00:28.027
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.094 --> 00:29.028
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.095 --> 00:30.330
{\an7}- Poo-poo.

00:34.801 --> 00:37.737
<i>[heavy-metal music]</i>

00:37.804 --> 00:44.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:44.911 --> 00:47.147
{\an1}- Yo, Chunk,
right on time, dude.

00:47.213 --> 00:48.915
- I slept in your driveway

00:48.982 --> 00:50.717
so I wouldn't be late.

00:50.784 --> 00:52.952
- Whoa. That's hard core, bro.

00:53.019 --> 00:54.687
{\an3}- Load it, drive it,
rig it, repeat.

00:54.754 --> 00:57.924
That's the life of a rock
and roll roadie, isn't it?

00:57.991 --> 00:59.626
- [grunting, panting]

00:59.692 --> 01:01.027
'Ello, 'ello, Chunk.

01:01.094 --> 01:04.030
Pip, pip, cheerio--oh!

01:04.096 --> 01:05.230
- Don't mind my dad.

01:05.298 --> 01:06.900
He spent one semester abroad,

01:06.966 --> 01:08.334
and he thinks he's a Brit.

01:08.401 --> 01:10.737
{\an3}- [chuckles]
That's all right, love.

01:10.804 --> 01:12.038
Wotcha, me China.

01:12.105 --> 01:13.973
All the Mae West
to the Duchess of Fife

01:14.040 --> 01:15.675
and the wee dustbin lids too.

01:15.742 --> 01:17.210
- Uh... Right!

01:17.277 --> 01:19.813
Uh, couldn't agree more!

01:19.879 --> 01:22.015
[engine revs]
- Catch ya later, Pop Star.

01:22.081 --> 01:24.083
- Good luck with
your audition, honey!

01:24.150 --> 01:25.919
"Wee dustbin lids."

01:25.985 --> 01:27.887
That must be in here somewhere.

01:27.954 --> 01:30.890
[rock music]

01:30.957 --> 01:33.493
♪ ♪

01:33.560 --> 01:36.095
- ♪ Dropping records
on a weekly basis ♪

01:36.162 --> 01:38.498
♪ ♪

01:38.565 --> 01:41.234
♪ Playing shows
in exotic places ♪

01:41.301 --> 01:43.770
♪ ♪

01:43.837 --> 01:46.673
♪ Rocking out
to a cheering crowd ♪

01:46.739 --> 01:49.209
♪ ♪

01:49.275 --> 01:52.045
♪ Hear them screaming,
"Luna Loud!" ♪

01:52.111 --> 01:53.980
♪ ♪

01:54.047 --> 01:56.449
♪ My favorite colors are
platinum and gold ♪

01:56.516 --> 01:59.452
♪ Being a rock star
never gets old ♪

01:59.519 --> 02:02.055
♪ My life is a dream ♪

02:02.121 --> 02:04.057
♪ A crazy rock and roll dream ♪

02:04.123 --> 02:11.364
♪ ♪

02:15.168 --> 02:17.203
Stage dive!

02:17.270 --> 02:18.538
[thud]

02:20.106 --> 02:21.474
Sorry, dude.

02:21.541 --> 02:23.776
I hope I passed the audition.

02:23.843 --> 02:25.745
- Oh, you did more than pass.

02:25.812 --> 02:28.915
{\an1}You're gonna be headlining
the Royal Rumble.

02:28.982 --> 02:30.783
Congratulations, dear.

02:30.850 --> 02:33.653
{\an3}- Smashing, love!
Your biggest gig yet!

02:33.720 --> 02:37.557
- Whoo! Next stop,
rock and roll fame!

02:37.624 --> 02:40.627
- Is--is that Chester Monk?
- The one and only.

02:40.693 --> 02:43.830
{\an3}Great to see you,
Ms. Vaporciyan.

02:43.897 --> 02:45.999
- Whoa! You know Chunk?

02:46.065 --> 02:47.534
- Well, I was his first teacher

02:47.600 --> 02:49.168
{\an3}when he moved here
from England.

02:49.235 --> 02:53.306
{\an3}I always thought he was
gonna be such a big rock star.

02:53.373 --> 02:55.575
{\an3}You know, he headlined
the Rumble too.

02:55.642 --> 02:56.910
- He did?

02:56.976 --> 02:58.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:58.545 --> 03:01.281
{\an1}Why didn't you tell me
you headlined the Rumble, dude?

03:01.347 --> 03:03.049
- Didn't wanna toot
me own horn,

03:03.116 --> 03:04.651
but yeah, it was quite a show.

03:04.717 --> 03:07.287
Five encores,
but who's counting?

03:07.353 --> 03:08.788
Have a butcher's
at me yearbook.

03:08.855 --> 03:10.490
{\an8}<i>[rock music</i>
<i>playing over radio]</i>

03:10.557 --> 03:13.893
{\an8}- "Next stop,
rock and roll fame"?

03:13.960 --> 03:16.429
{\an8}Next stop, rock and roll fame!

03:16.496 --> 03:18.998
{\an3}- Great minds think alike,
eh, love?

03:19.065 --> 03:20.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:20.767 --> 03:21.868
'Ello, governor.

03:21.935 --> 03:23.903
[tires screech]

03:23.970 --> 03:25.538
Just what I was fancying.

03:25.605 --> 03:28.942
{\an1}- Why is he grabbing
that junk off the road?

03:29.008 --> 03:30.209
<i>[tense music]</i>

03:30.276 --> 03:32.445
{\an1}What if I don't make it
as a rock star?

03:32.512 --> 03:35.715
I don't wanna end up
living in a van, man.

03:35.782 --> 03:39.352
{\an3}- So, uh, why do you wanna work
in a record store?

03:39.419 --> 03:41.788
{\an1}- Well, I really wanted
to be a rock star,

03:41.854 --> 03:44.290
but that's probably
never gonna happen,

03:44.357 --> 03:45.725
{\an1}so I figured
this is another way

03:45.792 --> 03:47.894
{\an1}I can share my love
of music with people.

03:47.961 --> 03:49.395
{\an3}- Right on.

03:49.462 --> 03:50.897
You're hired.

03:50.964 --> 03:53.066
<i>[rock music]</i>

03:53.132 --> 03:54.434
[door opens, bells jingle]

03:54.500 --> 03:56.736
{\an3}- Welcome, dude!
How can I help you?

03:56.803 --> 03:59.172
{\an1}- Do you have
Mick Swagger's new album?

03:59.238 --> 04:00.773
I hear he's pretty good.

04:00.840 --> 04:03.810
{\an3}- Pretty good?
Mick's basically a rock god!

04:03.876 --> 04:05.612
{\an3}But you can't just start
with his new stuff.

04:05.678 --> 04:07.480
You need to know where
the man's coming from.

04:07.547 --> 04:09.282
Let's start with
his first album,

04:09.349 --> 04:11.584
"Where I'm Coming From."
- Ahh!

04:11.651 --> 04:13.786
{\an1}- This is Mick's fifth album,
where he went reggae.

04:13.853 --> 04:16.089
{\an1}If you play it backwards,
it's a country album,

04:16.154 --> 04:17.923
{\an1}so it's actually
his fifth and sixth.

04:17.991 --> 04:19.225
- Ahh!

04:19.291 --> 04:20.827
{\an3}- Mick's ninth album
is super rare,

04:20.892 --> 04:23.596
{\an3}'cause instead of vinyl,
they made it out of hard candy.

04:23.663 --> 04:24.998
- Luna, you gotta chill out.

04:25.064 --> 04:27.367
- Dude, I'm with a customer.
[door opens]

04:27.433 --> 04:30.937
- You mean that customer?

04:31.004 --> 04:32.605
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:32.672 --> 04:34.273
Hey, I love your
enthusiasm, kid,

04:34.340 --> 04:37.010
{\an1}but it's also
why I'm firing you.

04:38.711 --> 04:41.180
{\an1}- So, I figure,
this is another way

04:41.247 --> 04:43.916
{\an1}I can share my love
of music with people.

04:43.983 --> 04:47.120
{\an3}- Cool.
You're my new afternoon DJ.

04:47.186 --> 04:49.155
- ♪ Ooh, girl, if I could ♪

04:49.222 --> 04:51.624
♪ Ooh, girl, give you the-- ♪
[record scratching]

04:51.691 --> 04:54.360
♪ Ooh, girl, if I could ♪
- Yeah, girl, sing it!

04:54.427 --> 04:56.229
- ♪ Ooh, girl, if I could ♪

04:56.295 --> 04:58.398
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, la, la, la ♪

04:58.464 --> 05:00.933
♪ Ooh, girl! World girl! ♪

05:01.000 --> 05:02.435
♪ You girl! ♪

05:04.404 --> 05:06.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:06.406 --> 05:08.741
{\an1}- Greetings,
third eldest sister.

05:08.808 --> 05:13.846
{\an1}Just making the rounds
for my weekly DNA cheek swabs.

05:13.913 --> 05:15.882
- [sighs]

05:17.150 --> 05:19.819
{\an1}- I don't typically acknowledge
human emotions,

05:19.886 --> 05:22.755
{\an1}but you seem
unusually dispirited.

05:22.822 --> 05:25.191
{\an3}- You're too young
to understand.

05:25.258 --> 05:27.827
- Pfft, tell that to
the Nobel Committee.

05:27.894 --> 05:29.028
- Respect.

05:29.095 --> 05:30.997
Well, I'm worried
about my future, dude.

05:31.064 --> 05:33.299
Making it as a rock star
seems impossible,

05:33.366 --> 05:36.602
but I can't find a fit anywhere
else in the music business.

05:36.669 --> 05:38.538
I just don't know
what to do now.

05:38.604 --> 05:40.973
- Hm, I would advise
a practical approach.

05:41.040 --> 05:43.476
According to
national labor statistics,

05:43.543 --> 05:45.745
the fastest growing fields
are health care,

05:45.812 --> 05:47.580
food service, and technology.

05:47.647 --> 05:49.782
I suggest you delve into those.

05:49.849 --> 05:52.085
{\an3}- I hear what you're
laying down, Sis.

05:52.151 --> 05:53.352
- Wish me luck.

05:53.419 --> 05:56.989
{\an1}Lola's next,
and she's a bit of a biter.

05:57.056 --> 05:59.325
<i>- Thanks for letting me</i>
<i>shadow you today.</i>

05:59.392 --> 06:01.527
- Sure, honey.
- Ready for this?

06:01.594 --> 06:04.664
- Actually, Flip, we've been
ready for you for ten years.

06:04.731 --> 06:06.132
- Don't bust my chops!

06:06.199 --> 06:08.901
You try running
a 24-hour convenience store.

06:08.968 --> 06:10.002
Ahh...

06:10.069 --> 06:11.604
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:11.671 --> 06:15.241
<i>[upbeat jazz music]</i>

06:15.308 --> 06:17.243
- [grunting]

06:17.310 --> 06:18.878
What is this?

06:18.945 --> 06:20.947
{\an1}- My meat molar!
The tooth fell out,

06:21.013 --> 06:24.450
{\an1}so I made a replacement
with some beef jerky.

06:25.418 --> 06:26.786
[thud]

06:26.853 --> 06:28.955
{\an1}- Thanks for letting me
check out the restaurant.

06:29.021 --> 06:30.423
- Sure thing, hon.

06:30.490 --> 06:31.524
[scooter whirs]

06:31.591 --> 06:32.792
Ooh, a customer.

06:32.859 --> 06:35.027
{\an3}Hey, why don't
you take this one?

06:35.094 --> 06:38.431
{\an3}- Here you are, ma'am.
One Cobb salad.

06:38.498 --> 06:40.533
- Hey, what's the dealio?

06:40.600 --> 06:42.201
I asked for extra bacon.

06:42.268 --> 06:44.437
- Oh, sorry. My bad.

06:44.504 --> 06:45.872
<i>[relaxing music]</i>

06:45.938 --> 06:49.475
{\an1}- [sniffs, groans]
This blue cheese smells whack.

06:49.542 --> 06:51.177
{\an3}- [sighs]

06:51.244 --> 06:53.079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:53.146 --> 06:56.015
{\an1}- Hey, why is there
so much bacon on this?

06:56.082 --> 06:57.383
- Are you kidding, dude?

06:57.450 --> 06:59.952
Fine, I'll fix it for you!

07:00.019 --> 07:02.388
{\an3}- Uh, you know what,
I got this one, honey.

07:02.455 --> 07:04.123
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:04.190 --> 07:06.993
- The tech field seems
pretty rad, Mr. Grouse.

07:07.059 --> 07:09.128
{\an1}Thanks for letting me
hang with you.

07:09.195 --> 07:10.630
- It would be a lot more rad

07:10.696 --> 07:12.498
if you stopped
fiddling with my desk!

07:12.565 --> 07:15.101
I'm trying to debug this code.

07:15.168 --> 07:16.402
[beeping]

07:16.469 --> 07:18.304
"Catastrophic error"?

07:18.371 --> 07:20.339
[groans] That's the berries.

07:20.406 --> 07:22.375
- Let me give it a try, brah.

07:22.441 --> 07:25.378
<i>[intense music]</i>

07:25.444 --> 07:27.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:27.446 --> 07:29.715
{\an1}- Holy Toledo.
How'd you pull that off?

07:29.782 --> 07:32.218
{\an3}- Guess I learned a thing
or two about computers

07:32.285 --> 07:33.619
from recording music.

07:33.686 --> 07:36.355
{\an1}- Well, you've got
a future here, young lady.

07:36.422 --> 07:38.090
- Really?
- You bet ya.

07:38.157 --> 07:39.458
And it's a heck of a gig.

07:39.525 --> 07:42.862
{\an1}Great job security
and a solid retirement plan!

07:42.929 --> 07:45.765
{\an3}- Sweet--sounds a lot better
than living in a van.

07:45.832 --> 07:49.435
{\an3}Plus, I see you get
Casual Fridays.

07:49.502 --> 07:51.404
- Eeh, casual what now?

07:51.470 --> 07:53.072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:53.139 --> 07:55.074
[trombone music]

07:55.141 --> 07:56.609
- Ms. V?

07:56.676 --> 07:57.977
I just wanted to tell you,

07:58.044 --> 08:00.346
I'm dropping out of
the Royal Rumble.

08:00.413 --> 08:02.281
[sad trombone music]

08:02.348 --> 08:05.184
I know I'm never gonna
make it as a rock star,

08:05.251 --> 08:06.786
so I'm done with music.

08:06.853 --> 08:08.487
I.T. is my jam now.

08:08.554 --> 08:09.922
It's a heck of a gig.

08:09.989 --> 08:12.959
{\an3}Great job security,
solid retirement plan.

08:13.025 --> 08:14.460
It's more practical.

08:14.527 --> 08:15.895
- Well, wait, Luna, honey,

08:15.962 --> 08:17.897
{\an1}you don't have to
give up music completely.

08:17.964 --> 08:20.066
Lots of people play as a hobby.

08:20.132 --> 08:22.535
{\an3}- Nah, it would just
break my heart,

08:22.602 --> 08:24.670
my achy, breaky heart.

08:24.737 --> 08:27.573
{\an3}Sorry to mess up
the Rumble, Ms. V.

08:29.408 --> 08:31.010
"Chunk &amp; the Pieces"?

08:31.077 --> 08:33.511
Uh, what's this?
- Chester gave me that.

08:33.578 --> 08:35.448
{\an1}His band is playing at
the Red Herring tonight.

08:35.514 --> 08:37.183
- Chunk has a band?

08:37.250 --> 08:40.052
{\an3}I thought he gave up music
a long time ago.

08:40.119 --> 08:42.020
[groovy rock music]

08:42.087 --> 08:44.490
- ♪ I'm a little East London ♪

08:44.557 --> 08:46.759
♪ And I'm a little
Royal Woods ♪

08:46.826 --> 08:49.862
♪ When it comes to
rock and roll ♪

08:49.929 --> 08:51.964
♪ I've got the goods ♪

08:52.031 --> 08:54.066
♪ You can call me Chester ♪

08:54.133 --> 08:56.736
♪ Or you can call me Chunk ♪

08:56.802 --> 08:59.472
♪ Either way, baby ♪

08:59.538 --> 09:01.874
♪ I've got the funk ♪

09:01.941 --> 09:04.877
Are you ready to get funky?
[crowd cheers]

09:04.944 --> 09:08.047
All right, let me
take it to the rinse cycle!

09:08.114 --> 09:11.350
♪ ♪

09:11.417 --> 09:13.853
- So that's what
he wanted it for.

09:13.920 --> 09:17.023
Go, Chunk! Rock on!

09:17.089 --> 09:20.660
♪ ♪

09:20.726 --> 09:22.528
That was awesome, dude!

09:22.595 --> 09:24.530
I had no idea you still played.

09:24.597 --> 09:26.899
- Yeah, once you get
the performing bug,

09:26.966 --> 09:29.001
{\an3}you just can't
shake it, can ya?

09:29.068 --> 09:31.237
{\an1}- Hey, I know
it's none of my biz,

09:31.304 --> 09:33.205
{\an1}but that stuff in your yearbook
made it seem like

09:33.272 --> 09:35.641
{\an1}being a rock star
was all you ever wanted.

09:35.708 --> 09:37.610
{\an1}Are you bummed
you didn't make it?

09:37.677 --> 09:38.978
- Who says I didn't make it?

09:39.045 --> 09:41.414
I may not be playing
in sold-out arenas,

09:41.480 --> 09:42.782
but I'm doing what I love.

09:42.848 --> 09:44.617
{\an3}That's my definition
of making it.

09:44.684 --> 09:46.585
{\an1}- Even if you have to
live in a van?

09:46.652 --> 09:49.021
{\an1}I mean, no offense.
It--it's a sweet van.

09:49.088 --> 09:51.857
{\an3}- [chuckles]
I don't live in it, love.

09:51.924 --> 09:53.292
I got me own flat.

09:53.359 --> 09:55.061
- What?
- [chuckles]

09:55.127 --> 09:58.464
{\an3}I only sleep in my van
the night before a big gig.

09:58.531 --> 09:59.765
Talking of gigs,

09:59.832 --> 10:01.567
{\an3}you all sorted
for the big Rumble?

10:01.634 --> 10:03.869
- Well, I am now!
- Brilliant.

10:03.936 --> 10:06.539
{\an3}Just let me know
how many guitars you need.

10:06.605 --> 10:09.542
[upbeat rock music]

10:09.608 --> 10:14.180
♪ ♪

10:14.246 --> 10:17.316
- ♪ Got the rock and roll bug,
and I just can't shake it ♪

10:17.383 --> 10:20.019
♪ ♪

10:20.086 --> 10:22.755
♪ Follow your heart
if you really wanna make it ♪

10:22.822 --> 10:24.957
♪ ♪

10:25.024 --> 10:28.227
♪ I tried my hand
at dental hygiene ♪

10:28.294 --> 10:30.162
♪ ♪

10:30.229 --> 10:33.566
♪ But at the end of the day
it just wasn't my scene ♪

10:33.632 --> 10:35.735
♪ ♪

10:35.801 --> 10:37.670
♪ You can live your life
full of doubt ♪

10:37.737 --> 10:41.273
♪ Or you can do what you love,
and it'll all work out ♪

10:41.340 --> 10:42.708
♪ ♪

10:42.775 --> 10:46.045
♪ My life is a dream ♪

10:46.112 --> 10:48.581
♪ The greatest
rock and roll dream ♪

10:48.647 --> 10:50.583
♪ ♪

10:50.649 --> 10:52.351
Ladies and gentlemen!

10:52.418 --> 10:55.354
{\an3}We've got some Rumble Royalty
in the house!

10:55.421 --> 10:58.691
{\an3}Give it up for
Chester "Chunk" Monk!

10:58.758 --> 11:00.459
[crowd cheers]

11:00.526 --> 11:01.994
♪ ♪

11:02.061 --> 11:04.597
both: ♪ You can live
your life full of doubt ♪

11:04.663 --> 11:08.701
♪ Or you can do what you love,
and it'll all work out ♪

11:08.768 --> 11:11.470
♪ My life is a dream ♪

11:11.537 --> 11:13.739
- ♪ The greatest
rock and roll dream! ♪

11:13.806 --> 11:15.875
♪ ♪

11:15.941 --> 11:18.677
[cheers and applause]

11:22.515 --> 11:25.384
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

11:25.451 --> 11:30.389
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:30.456 --> 11:32.091
[school bell ringing]

11:32.158 --> 11:34.727
[clock ticking]

11:34.794 --> 11:35.561
- Mmm...

11:35.628 --> 11:38.998
mac and cheese bites.

11:39.065 --> 11:41.867
{\an3}- Hey, psst, Lincoln,
what'd you get for number one?

11:41.934 --> 11:44.637
- Mac and cheese.

11:44.703 --> 11:46.272
- Thanks, buddy.
- Really?

11:46.338 --> 11:49.542
{\an3}I thought the Native Americans
gave the pilgrims corn.

11:49.608 --> 11:51.477
{\an1}- If Lincoln says
mac and cheese,

11:51.544 --> 11:53.279
that's good enough for me.

11:53.345 --> 11:54.747
- I can't focus at all today.

11:54.814 --> 11:56.515
Last night, Dad made his famous

11:56.582 --> 11:58.084
mac and cheese bites
for dinner,

11:58.150 --> 12:00.553
and in order to make
all that cheesy goodness last,

12:00.619 --> 12:02.555
I saved three bites
for after school.

12:02.621 --> 12:03.556
But if I'm gonna
get through this day

12:03.622 --> 12:05.157
without losing my mind,

12:05.224 --> 12:07.460
I'm just gonna have to
stop thinking about them.

12:07.526 --> 12:08.861
<i>- Would the following students</i>

12:08.928 --> 12:10.496
<i>please report to</i>
<i>the principal's office?</i>

12:10.563 --> 12:12.965
<i>Mac and Chaz?</i>

12:13.032 --> 12:14.967
{\an3}- All right, everyone,
pencils down,

12:15.034 --> 12:16.735
{\an3}and let's go over
the worksheet.

12:16.802 --> 12:18.671
{\an3}Who has the answer
to number one?

12:18.737 --> 12:21.340
{\an3}- Oh! Oh! Me!
It's mac and cheese.

12:21.407 --> 12:23.609
And if I'm wrong,
you can flunk me.

12:23.676 --> 12:25.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:25.377 --> 12:26.879
- ♪ Today's the big day ♪

12:26.946 --> 12:28.514
♪ Just gotta chill
the duck liver pâté ♪

12:28.581 --> 12:30.583
♪ I'll show 'em
that I'm a star ♪

12:30.649 --> 12:32.918
♪ With my yummy take
on caviar ♪

12:32.985 --> 12:35.521
{\an3}- I love that
confidence, honey.

12:35.588 --> 12:37.189
{\an3}When is the investor
getting here?

12:37.256 --> 12:38.324
- In a few hours.

12:38.390 --> 12:39.758
{\an1}Just think,
if he likes my food,

12:39.825 --> 12:42.228
I can open my own restaurant!

12:42.294 --> 12:44.163
Here, try this foie gras foam.

12:44.230 --> 12:45.865
{\an3}- [grunts]

12:45.931 --> 12:47.766
- And here's the second course.

12:47.833 --> 12:51.237
{\an3}- [sniffing]
Uh, this is just air in a jar.

12:51.303 --> 12:53.272
- Lemon air in a jar.

12:53.339 --> 12:55.374
High end, yet low-cal.

12:55.441 --> 12:56.842
- Honey, no offense,

12:56.909 --> 12:59.845
but why are you making
all this showy stuff?

12:59.912 --> 13:02.414
{\an3}What's wrong with
your famous Lynn-sagna?

13:02.481 --> 13:04.617
- Honey, this is
Timothy McCole.

13:04.683 --> 13:06.252
{\an1}This guy travels
all over the world,

13:06.318 --> 13:07.953
tasting exciting
and exotic food.

13:08.020 --> 13:10.322
{\an1}I--I--I can't just serve him
a--a hunk of noodles.

13:10.389 --> 13:13.459
- Well, I like the hunk
who made those noodles,

13:13.526 --> 13:16.128
{\an3}and I think anything
he cooks is delicious.

13:16.195 --> 13:17.496
[smooches]

13:17.563 --> 13:19.198
{\an1}- Can you say that again
when he's here?

13:19.265 --> 13:20.633
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:20.699 --> 13:22.935
- Mac and cheese...

13:23.002 --> 13:25.604
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:27.306 --> 13:28.407
Two bites?

13:28.474 --> 13:31.443
{\an3}I saved three!
[growls]

13:31.510 --> 13:32.745
{\an3}All right,
which of you vultures

13:32.811 --> 13:34.713
{\an3}swiped one of my
mac and cheese bites?

13:34.780 --> 13:36.182
{\an3}If you guys wanted
one so badly,

13:36.248 --> 13:37.983
{\an3}you should've saved
some of your own.

13:38.050 --> 13:39.985
- I'm not saying
it was me--

13:40.052 --> 13:41.887
[belches]
But if I did take one,

13:41.954 --> 13:43.322
I only did it
'cause Lola ate

13:43.389 --> 13:44.723
the rest of Dad's
tater tot bake.

13:44.790 --> 13:46.091
I was saving that!

13:46.158 --> 13:48.327
{\an1}- I'm not copping to
eating the tater tot bake,

13:48.394 --> 13:49.728
but if I did, it was because

13:49.795 --> 13:52.064
{\an1}Luan ate the last slice
of Dad's pie,

13:52.131 --> 13:53.832
which I was saving!

13:53.899 --> 13:55.701
- Actually, I didn't eat it.

13:55.768 --> 13:59.838
- Oh, my bad.
- I smashed it in Lynn's face.

13:59.905 --> 14:01.273
{\an1}- [growls]

14:01.340 --> 14:03.809
{\an3}- Guys, how do you not see
that this is a problem?

14:03.876 --> 14:05.911
{\an3}Our fridge is like
the wild west.

14:05.978 --> 14:09.148
- Look, Lincoln, nobody likes
having their leftovers swiped,

14:09.215 --> 14:10.583
but we're a big family.

14:10.649 --> 14:11.917
You can't expect to protect

14:11.984 --> 14:14.153
every little bite of food
that you want.

14:14.220 --> 14:16.355
- Oh, can't I?

14:16.422 --> 14:18.624
- No, you can't.

14:18.691 --> 14:20.926
<i>[laidback jazz music]</i>

14:20.993 --> 14:23.796
<i>- Hmm, I really want one of</i>
<i>those mac and cheese bites,</i>

14:23.862 --> 14:25.731
<i>but Lincoln's gonna</i>
<i>have a conniption.</i>

14:25.798 --> 14:27.366
<i>But then again,</i>
<i>watching Lincoln</i>

14:27.433 --> 14:30.569
<i>have a conniption is fun.</i>

14:30.636 --> 14:32.438
Ow!

14:32.504 --> 14:34.540
- That'll teach her.

14:34.607 --> 14:37.476
{\an1}- Oh, so we're protecting
our stuff now, huh?

14:37.543 --> 14:40.145
Fine by me.

14:40.212 --> 14:41.547
- [gasps]

14:41.614 --> 14:43.582
<i>Ooh, one of Dad's</i>
<i>yummy brownies.</i>

14:43.649 --> 14:45.718
<i>Oh, wait,</i>
<i>didn't Luan call this?</i>

14:45.784 --> 14:47.119
<i>Well, she won't mind</i>

14:47.186 --> 14:50.022
<i>if I just break off</i>
<i>a little corner.</i>

14:50.089 --> 14:52.358
{\an3}Oh-ho! Ow!

14:52.424 --> 14:55.394
- The gloves are off now.
[laughs]

14:55.461 --> 14:58.063
<i>- Luan put that there</i>
<i>to protect her leftovers?</i>

14:58.130 --> 15:00.366
<i>Well, I can play</i>
<i>that game too.</i>

15:00.432 --> 15:03.202
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

15:03.269 --> 15:04.370
[beeping]

15:04.436 --> 15:05.371
[bang]

15:05.437 --> 15:12.678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:14.446 --> 15:16.548
[electric crackling]
- Ahh!

15:16.615 --> 15:18.150
[chomp]

15:18.217 --> 15:19.685
- Ahh!

15:19.752 --> 15:22.521
- That's it--you guys really
crossed the line this time.

15:22.588 --> 15:25.891
{\an1}- I'd say that line was crossed
when this happened, brah.

15:25.958 --> 15:28.294
- Or this!
- Or this!

15:28.360 --> 15:30.229
{\an1}- Ga, ga!

15:30.296 --> 15:32.898
- This is crazy.
We can't go on like this.

15:32.965 --> 15:35.200
If someone could
gently let me down,

15:35.267 --> 15:37.336
I think I have an idea.

15:37.403 --> 15:38.937
[grunts]
[thud]

15:39.004 --> 15:40.239
I think we can all agree,

15:40.306 --> 15:42.608
basic order
needs to be restored,

15:42.675 --> 15:44.376
so with an assist from Lisa,

15:44.443 --> 15:46.578
I came up with a plan.

15:46.645 --> 15:48.881
- Ah!
- Sorry.

15:48.947 --> 15:50.249
{\an8}Per Lincoln's request,

15:50.316 --> 15:52.618
{\an7}I calculated the refrigerator's
cubic footage,

15:52.685 --> 15:55.821
{\an7}and divided it into
11 equally-sized zones,

15:55.888 --> 15:57.723
{\an8}creating the optimal conditions

15:57.790 --> 16:00.926
{\an7}for what I like to call
Dairy Détente.

16:00.993 --> 16:03.896
{\an8}- Everybody gets a zone,
and the genius part is

16:03.962 --> 16:06.432
{\an8}that no one can mistake
theirs for someone else's,

16:06.498 --> 16:07.900
{\an8}because they're color coded.

16:07.966 --> 16:09.501
{\an8}<i>[enchanting music]</i>

16:09.568 --> 16:11.270
{\an8}all: Ooh...

16:11.337 --> 16:14.206
- All we have to do now is
divide up Dad's leftovers

16:14.273 --> 16:16.041
and put them in our zones.

16:17.509 --> 16:19.845
[yelling]

16:19.912 --> 16:21.213
- I call Dad's stuffed peppers!

16:21.280 --> 16:22.848
- And I got dibs on
his fried chicken!

16:22.915 --> 16:24.283
- I get his mine-strone!

16:24.350 --> 16:27.252
{\an1}- Uh, Leni, it's pronounced
mi-ne-stró-ne.

16:27.319 --> 16:29.388
- I call it mine-strone,

16:29.455 --> 16:31.657
'cause it's mine.

16:32.624 --> 16:34.360
{\an3}- Nice job.
Thanks for the assist.

16:34.426 --> 16:35.527
- You're welcome.

16:35.594 --> 16:36.862
{\an1}For payment,
I will happily accept

16:36.929 --> 16:38.731
{\an1}your last
mac and cheese bite.

16:38.797 --> 16:40.632
- Not a chance.

16:40.699 --> 16:43.702
- [humming]

16:43.769 --> 16:45.971
♪ Wait till he tries
my uni surprise ♪

16:46.038 --> 16:48.474
♪ This organic beet juice
will open his eyes ♪

16:48.540 --> 16:50.876
♪ That investor guy
will feel like a royal ♪

16:50.943 --> 16:52.811
♪ When he tastes
my risotto with-- ♪

16:52.878 --> 16:54.713
Dang it!
I forgot the truffle oil!

16:54.780 --> 16:57.015
Come on, Lynn,
you're better than that.

16:58.050 --> 17:00.119
- Next stop: yellow zone!

17:00.185 --> 17:02.688
Can't wait to dig into
Dad's mashed potatoes.

17:02.755 --> 17:05.057
- And my destination
is the green zone,

17:05.124 --> 17:08.993
where I intend to feast on
father's savory meatloaf.

17:09.060 --> 17:10.561
Nom-nom.

17:10.628 --> 17:12.030
- Ew, gross.

17:12.097 --> 17:14.031
{\an8}Someone put something
in my zone called uni,

17:14.098 --> 17:16.201
{\an8}whatever that is.
- That would be a low fat,

17:16.268 --> 17:19.538
{\an9}high protein globular animal
in the Echinoidea class.

17:19.605 --> 17:21.473
{\an8}Street name: sea urchin.

17:21.540 --> 17:23.675
{\an8}- Well, see ya later!

17:23.742 --> 17:25.577
{\an3}[cat meows]

17:25.644 --> 17:27.079
[munching]

17:27.146 --> 17:28.881
{\an1}Must be one of Lori's
gross health foods,

17:28.947 --> 17:32.551
{\an1}and it does not
belong in my zone.

17:32.618 --> 17:34.853
- Ick, Lucy's homemade blood

17:34.920 --> 17:36.889
does not belong in my zone.

17:36.955 --> 17:38.757
Buh-bye.
[cat meows]

17:38.824 --> 17:40.826
<i>[upbeat jazz music]</i>

17:40.893 --> 17:43.962
- Ew! What is this black goo?

17:44.029 --> 17:46.165
[sniffs]
Ew, it smells fishy.

17:46.231 --> 17:49.201
Must be Lana's bait.
Not in my zone.

17:49.268 --> 17:50.636
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:50.702 --> 17:52.237
- "Duck liver pate"?

17:52.304 --> 17:55.207
Ew! Lisa!
If you wanna dissect animals,

17:55.274 --> 17:58.143
don't put their icky organs
in my zone.

17:58.210 --> 18:00.078
[cat groans]

18:00.145 --> 18:01.547
{\an3}[purrs]

18:01.613 --> 18:03.949
[tires screech]
- If they can't be on time,

18:04.016 --> 18:07.319
just cancel the appointment,
and move my 3:15 to 3:00,

18:07.386 --> 18:08.754
my 4:15 to 4:00,

18:08.821 --> 18:10.923
and my pedicure to 5:00.

18:10.989 --> 18:13.959
{\an1}- Oh, hi there--Lynn Loud Sr.
I am so glad to meet--

18:14.026 --> 18:15.694
- Timothy McCole,
but call me Tim,

18:15.761 --> 18:17.129
{\an3}'cause Timothy takes
more time to say,

18:17.196 --> 18:19.832
{\an3}and time is the one thing
I don't have.

18:19.898 --> 18:22.034
{\an3}Now, let's see
what you got for me.

18:22.100 --> 18:23.235
- Uh, don't worry, Tim,

18:23.302 --> 18:25.370
{\an1}you'll be eating
before you know it.

18:26.472 --> 18:27.706
[screams]

18:27.773 --> 18:29.408
<i>[dramatic musical stings]</i>

18:29.475 --> 18:32.177
- Is everything all right?
- Um--uh, of course!

18:32.244 --> 18:34.813
I--I--I always scream
when I open the fridge.

18:34.880 --> 18:38.083
See?
[screaming]

18:38.150 --> 18:41.753
{\an3}- Okay, I guess every chef
has his own style.

18:41.820 --> 18:43.755
- Uh, Tim, can I interest you

18:43.822 --> 18:45.491
in, uh, apéritif?
[chuckles]

18:45.557 --> 18:48.360
- Well, I'd really rather--
- Good, here's a juice box.

18:48.427 --> 18:50.062
Go sit down.

18:50.128 --> 18:52.798
{\an1}I'll call you
once dinner's ready.

18:52.865 --> 18:55.467
Where are all
my ding dang ingredients?

18:55.534 --> 18:57.936
{\an3}- Dad, are you okay?
We heard a woman yelling.

18:58.003 --> 18:59.671
- No, I'm not okay.

18:59.738 --> 19:01.240
There's an investor
in the living room

19:01.306 --> 19:04.376
waiting to try my food, and
all my ingredients are gone!

19:04.443 --> 19:05.811
[cat groans, vomits]

19:05.878 --> 19:08.514
Well, there's my pâté...

19:08.580 --> 19:09.848
And my caviar...

19:09.915 --> 19:11.416
And my uni.

19:11.483 --> 19:13.919
Cliff, how did you get
your paws on my ingredients?

19:13.986 --> 19:15.621
- It wasn't Cliff's fault, Dad.

19:15.687 --> 19:17.189
We threw out your ingredients.

19:17.256 --> 19:19.057
{\an3}He must've gotten them
out of the trash.

19:19.124 --> 19:21.026
{\an1}- What?
Wh--why would you do that?

19:21.093 --> 19:23.328
- We didn't know
they were yours.

19:23.395 --> 19:26.565
{\an8}- See, we kinda divided
the fridge into zones,

19:26.632 --> 19:29.234
{\an9}because we'd been stealing
each other's leftovers.

19:29.301 --> 19:31.370
{\an9}- So when we found
your stuff in our zones,

19:31.436 --> 19:33.772
{\an9}we assumed someone
was violating the system.

19:33.839 --> 19:36.141
{\an1}- You kids know I love your
creative conflict resolutions,

19:36.208 --> 19:38.544
but now I have nothing
to serve my investor!

19:38.610 --> 19:40.112
- [slurping]

19:40.178 --> 19:42.114
{\an1}- And he's almost done
with his juice box!

19:42.180 --> 19:43.515
- We're sorry, Dad.

19:43.582 --> 19:45.684
{\an3}We never meant for something
like this to happen.

19:45.751 --> 19:47.085
{\an1}- [sighs]
Well...

19:47.152 --> 19:49.454
{\an1}I guess my restaurant dreams
are in the toilet.

19:49.521 --> 19:51.256
I better go tell No-Time Tim

19:51.323 --> 19:53.458
his afternoon just opened up.

19:53.525 --> 19:54.826
- Dad, wait!

19:54.893 --> 19:56.695
What if you serve him
your leftovers!

19:56.762 --> 19:58.530
- Yeah, that's a great idea.

19:58.597 --> 20:00.432
{\an1}- You can take the stuffed
pepper I've been saving.

20:00.499 --> 20:02.301
{\an7}- And, uh, I can part
with your meatloaf.

20:02.367 --> 20:03.835
{\an8}- And I'll give you this soup!

20:03.902 --> 20:06.772
{\an8}Mine-strone is now your-strone.

20:06.838 --> 20:08.340
{\an3}- Oh, that's a nice
thought, guys,

20:08.407 --> 20:10.108
but Tim won't want any of that.

20:10.175 --> 20:13.178
{\an3}He's used to eating the most
amazing food in the world.

20:13.245 --> 20:16.615
{\an1}- But your leftovers are the
most amazing food in the world.

20:16.682 --> 20:18.050
- Truth, Pop Star.

20:18.116 --> 20:20.218
{\an1}Look what we did
to keep 'em to ourselves.

20:20.285 --> 20:21.887
- [sniffs]
Well...

20:21.954 --> 20:24.256
I guess it's worth a shot.

20:24.323 --> 20:26.024
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:26.091 --> 20:29.027
- [chomps, munching]

20:29.094 --> 20:32.731
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:32.798 --> 20:34.166
[gulps]

20:34.232 --> 20:36.835
Well, Lynn, I'm gonna
give it to you straight.

20:36.902 --> 20:39.271
This is one of...

20:39.338 --> 20:42.040
The best meals I've ever eaten!

20:42.107 --> 20:44.743
- I knew it was a dumb idea.
I should've never served it!

20:44.810 --> 20:46.211
I--um, wait, what?

20:46.278 --> 20:47.779
- I've been all over the world,

20:47.846 --> 20:50.482
{\an1}and every chef serves me
the same thing.

20:50.549 --> 20:52.818
Caviar, pâté, uni--

20:52.884 --> 20:55.153
it's boring and uninspired.

20:55.220 --> 20:56.955
{\an1}Do you know
at the last place I ate,

20:57.022 --> 20:59.958
{\an1}the chef served me
air in a jar?

21:00.025 --> 21:02.661
- Pfft! Ha! What a bozo!

21:02.728 --> 21:04.630
- But your food is classic,

21:04.696 --> 21:06.164
comforting, and delicious,

21:06.231 --> 21:08.100
{\an1}and when you travel
as much as I do,

21:08.166 --> 21:12.137
there's nothing better than
food that tastes like home.

21:12.204 --> 21:15.774
{\an1}Ooh, I wanna be in
the Lynn Loud business!

21:15.841 --> 21:17.809
- Wow, ha, thank you, Tim.

21:17.876 --> 21:19.845
I--I--I don't know what to say!

21:19.911 --> 21:21.713
- I don't do hugs.

21:22.981 --> 21:25.050
[phone rings]
You got Tim.

21:25.117 --> 21:27.285
- We do hugs!

21:27.352 --> 21:29.221
- [exhaling]
- So, how did it go?

21:29.287 --> 21:31.123
- Ah, Dad kicked butt!

21:31.189 --> 21:32.591
- Yeah, I'm one step closer

21:32.658 --> 21:34.726
to my dream of
owning a restaurant.

21:34.793 --> 21:36.561
- I'm so proud of you, honey!

21:36.628 --> 21:39.464
{\an3}I guess he liked your uni
and your lemon air.

21:39.531 --> 21:42.200
- Actually, he liked
my leftover Lynn-sagna,

21:42.267 --> 21:43.735
just like you said.

21:43.802 --> 21:45.937
{\an7}- And all his
other leftovers too!

21:46.004 --> 21:47.205
{\an8}- That's wonderful!

21:47.272 --> 21:48.607
This calls for a celebration.

21:48.674 --> 21:50.809
Who wants some of
Dad's chocolate cake?

21:50.876 --> 21:52.377
all: Me!

21:52.444 --> 21:54.680
- Wait, I didn't see any
chocolate cake in the fridge.

21:54.746 --> 21:58.050
- Well, that's because
I stashed it under the couch.

21:58.116 --> 22:00.619
What, I can't claim
any leftovers?

22:00.686 --> 22:02.854
- I'll go score us some!
- Lynn, wait!

22:02.921 --> 22:04.623
[bang]
- Ahh!

22:10.929 --> 22:12.464
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:12.531 --> 22:14.399
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:14.466 --> 22:16.468
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.535 --> 22:19.471
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.538 --> 22:23.475
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.542 --> 22:25.010
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:25.077 --> 22:26.778
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.845 --> 22:28.146
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:28.213 --> 22:29.481
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line</i>
<i>to take a pee ♪</i>

22:29.548 --> 22:30.716
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.782 --> 22:32.851
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.918 --> 22:35.153
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.220 --> 22:36.922
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
